lead_paragraph: ... isn't nearly as severe as a casual reading of the news might suggest. Or more accurately: Spain's economy is a mess, with immense unemployment, but there has actually been remarkably little contagion so far from Greek concerns. It comes as a bit of a shock, actually, to discover that the interest rate on Spanish 10-years is only 4.03 percent; it's up about 25 basis points since Greece went pear-shaped, but that's not bad, considering.
snippet: Spain is actually doing quite well in terms of maintaining fiscal credibility.
